<dec f='include/FLAC/format.h' l='1015' type='FLAC__bool FLAC__format_picture_is_legal(const FLAC__StreamMetadata_Picture * picture, const char ** violation)'/>
<doc f='include/FLAC/format.h' l='999'>/** Check picture data to see if it conforms to the FLAC specification.
 *  See the format specification for limits on the contents of the
 *  PICTURE block.
 *
 * \param picture    A pointer to existing picture data to be checked.
 * \param violation  Address of a pointer to a string.  If there is a
 *                   violation, a pointer to a string explanation of the
 *                   violation will be returned here. \a violation may be
 *                   \c NULL if you don&apos;t need the returned string.  Do not
 *                   free the returned string; it will always point to static
 *                   data.
 * \assert
 *    \code picture != NULL \endcode
 * \retval FLAC__bool
 *    \c false if picture data is illegal, else \c true.
 */</doc>
